It's more than a blessing to have you as my mother and i don't think i thank you enough for everything you do for me. I've been so busy with school that i just haven't had the time to tell you how much I appreciate you. I know it shouldn't be that way. You deserve to know how much you daughter looks up to you and loves you.
.
You've been a single mom since i don't even know when and yet you're the best one out there. Not many people can give their children all the support, love, and encouragement they need while going through many others trials life has to offer. I know it must not be easy to be such a great mom but you make it look like a piece of cake.
.
You have taught me a lot. You taught me happiness comes from within and that I don't need a man to complete me. You taught me that if I work hard, I can achieve anything. You taught me how important it is to educate myself both in school and in a real world. You taught me to be lighthearted and to not take my self too seriously. Thank you for everything you've taught me over the years by words and example. 
And if i can grow to be half the woman you are, that will be enough for me.
.
